  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You learn how to effectively read and track your prey. Once on each of your turns, you can choose a creature you can see within 120 feet and mark it as your quarry (no action required). For the next hour, you gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Once per turn, when you hit the target with a weapon attack, you can deal [[/r 1d4]] additional damage to it of the same type as the weapon's damage. </li>\n<li>You have advantage on any Wisdom (Perception) or Wisdom (Survival) check you make to find it while it's on the same planet as you.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can only have one creature marked in this way at a time. You can mark creatures in this way a number of times equal to half your proficiency bonus, rounded up. You regain all expended uses when you complete a long rest.</p>",
